Regarding age group segmentation, pediatric nursing care and geriatric nursing care play vital roles in meeting the healthcare needs of distinct patient populations. Pediatric nursing care ensures specialized and compassionate care for infants, children, and adolescents, focusing on their unique health requirements. In contrast, geriatric nursing care is essential for addressing the complex health issues faced by elderly individuals, encompassing long-term care management, chronic disease treatment, and end-of-life care. The differentiation in age group segments underscores the importance of tailoring nursing care services to specific age demographics, thereby optimizing patient outcomes and satisfaction.

